A customer has expressed concern that Confluence does not alert a user that the attachment they are adding is going to be versioned. 

When working with pages that contain many attachments their users have gone to add a new attachment which happeend to have the same name as an existing attachment. As there was no warning, they unwittingly overwrote a document with the same name.

The customer asked if Confluence could alert the user that the attachment is about to become the latest version of an existing attachment.

